value: [Music]
conquered him by the ruled bridge that
arched the flood their flag to april's
breeze unfurled here once the embattled
farmers stood and fired the shot heard
round the world the foe long since in
silence slept alike the Conqueror silent
sleeps and time the ruined bridge has
swept down the dark stream that seaward
creeps on this green Bank by this soft
stream we set today a votive stone that
memory may their deed redeem when like
our sires our sons are gone spirit that
made those heroes dare to die and leave
their children free bid time and nature
gently spare the shaft we raised to them
and thee
